title: AWS S3: Traffic Stats
agents: aws
catalog: cloud/aws
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors number bytes downloaded and uploaded,
 that contain a request body, for requests made to an
 AWS S3 bucket.
 To make this check work you have to configure the related
 special agent {Amazon Web Services (AWS)}.

 This check is always OK.

 You have to enable requests metrics in AWS/S3 console. This
 is a paid feature

item:
 Name of the instance

inventory:
 One service is created for each bucket if all required metrics
 (BytesDownloaded, BytesUploaded) are given.

